messages.content: What are the nodes included in the ComfyUI Sokes Nodes suite?
ComfyUI Sokes Nodes suite includes two nodes: 'Current Date with Custom Formatting' and 'Empty Latent Selector (9 Inputs)'.
What is the purpose of the 'Current Date with Custom Formatting' node in ComfyUI Sokes Nodes?
The 'Current Date with Custom Formatting' node is useful for file saving organization, allowing a customizable formatting, for example 'YYYY-MM-DD' format.
How does the 'Empty Latent Selector (9 Inputs)' node work in ComfyUI Sokes Nodes?
The 'Empty Latent Selector (9 Inputs)' node is designed for exporting a random latent dimensionality based on a fixed set of inputs.
How do I install the ComfyUI Sokes Nodes?

To install ComfyUI Sokes Nodes, you need to navigate to ComfyUI/custom_nodes/ directory in your terminal or command line interface and run 'git clone https://github.com/m-sokes/ComfyUI-Sokes-Nodes.git'. Then, restart ComfyUI.
ComfyUI is a node-based backend and GUI for Stable Diffusion.
What is the recommended extension for ComfyUI?
The recommended extension for ComfyUI is [ComfyUI-Manager](https://github.com/ltdrdata/ComfyUI-Manager).
What are the future node concepts planned for ComfyUI Sokes Nodes?
A future node concept planned for ComfyUI Sokes Nodes is an SDXL Prompt Styler node with custom categories based on JSON file(s).
